<br>
I don't necessarily have a problem with going to a raiding zone like Temple of Veeshan and seeing raid spam in public channels; however, there are important things that are said in public channels in the Plane of Nightmare (ie, train announcements, etc.) which make it upsetting when a guild is spamming /shout with all capital letters telling people to move from point A to point B.<br>
<br>
As Amato told me when I asked him about it, it's not necessarily illegal (unless a GM decides it's a zone disruption -- which could be possible with certain GMs), but it's very rude.   <br>
<br>
Why be rude when you don't have to?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aurianne>Aurianne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mana Whore</span><br>  Posts: 1408<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/8/02 5:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1813.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /shout as a raid channel in PoP?  /boggle</span><hr size=1> Unless they've completely rewritten channel code since I quit, there's a serious lag on chat channels. As much as 3 seconds, not even mentionning messages that get lost. For something like a CH chain, that's simply unacceptable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fydar>Fydar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/8/02 5:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1813.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /shout as a raid channel in PoP?  /boggle</span><hr size=1> The simple answer is, tradition.  /shout is red, people are used to seeing it and reading it while mentally filtering other channels.<br>
<br>
If you must have everyone's attention or risk wasting time due to wipe or reclearing, would you use /rsay and risk someone missing it cause they went ld and never got reinvited, or would you /shout and KNOW that everyone in the zone saw it.<br>
